The neuropeptide Neurotensin (NT) is a 13-amino acid peptide that exerts neuromodulatory functions in the central nervous system and endocrine/paracrine actions in the periphery.Neurotensin (NT) exerts its intracellular effect by interacting with 3 differ-
ent receptors. Two of these receptors (NTR1 and NTR2) belong to the G protein coupled receptor family,whereas the third one (NTR3) is a type I receptor with a single transmembrane domain.